ZH: 我每个月的工资涨了500块。
EN: My salary increased by 500 yuan per month.
ZH: 这份工作可以拿到一份不错的工资。
EN: This job offers a decent salary.
ZH: 她的工资比我高。
EN: Her salary is higher than mine.
ZH: 我期望能升职加薪。
EN: I hope to get a promotion and a raise.
ZH: 虽然工资低，但是挺有意思的工作。
EN: The job is interesting, even though the salary is low.
ZH: 我的工资单还没发下来。
EN: I haven't received my payslip yet.
ZH: 他总是抱怨工资太低。
EN: He always complains about his low salary.
ZH: 这份工作工资待遇丰厚。
EN: This job offers a generous salary.
ZH: 她在公司的工资等级最高。
EN: She has the highest salary grade in the company.
ZH: 我对工资待遇很满意。
EN: I am satisfied with my salary package.
ZH: 她为了工资不择手段。
EN: She will do anything for the sake of money.
ZH: 这个人是为了工资才来的。
EN: This person came for the salary alone.
ZH: 工资是劳动人民的一份辛苦劳动的回报。
EN: Salary is a reward for the hard work of the working class.
ZH: 感谢您按时支付工资。
EN: Thank you for paying the salary on time.
ZH: 她的工资根据工作表现而定。
EN: Her salary is based on job performance.
ZH: 如果你不满意工资，可以提出申请加薪。
EN: If you are not satisfied with your salary, you can apply for a raise.
ZH: 他的工资超出了我们的预算。
EN: His salary exceeds our budget.
ZH: 现在的工资跟以前相比涨了很多。
EN: The current salary has increased a lot compared to before.
ZH: 工资支付有时会遇到延迟。
EN: Salary payments can sometimes be delayed.
ZH: 我很享受拿到工资的那种成就感。
EN: I really enjoy the sense of accomplishment when receiving my salary.
